        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 18 at 10:03PM CDT by NWS Memphis TN</headline>
        <description>At 1002 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Fair Oaks, or 16 miles southeast of Augusta, moving east at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Wynne, Village Creek State Park, Cherry Valley, Caldwell, Colt, Fair
Oaks, Vanndale, Hydrick, Birdeye, Rosenbaum, River Front, Fitzgerald
Crossing, Crow Creek, Wittsburg, Tilton, Brushy Lake, McElroy,
Mersman, Kinton, and Fair Field.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
